## Quick Commands

### Environment Setup
```bash
# Activate conda environment
conda activate <your_env_name>

# Navigate to cruijff_kit
cd <path_to_cruijff_kit>

# Check git status
git status

# Pull latest changes
git pull
```

### Fine-tuning
```bash
# Navigate to task directory
cd tasks/capitalization/

# Generate configs and SLURM script
python ../../tools/torchtune/setup_finetune.py

# Submit job
sbatch finetune.slurm

# Check job status
squeue -u <your_username>

# Monitor specific job
scontrol show job <job_id>
```

### Evaluation
```bash
# Setup inspect for a checkpoint
python ../../tools/inspect/setup_inspect.py --finetune_epoch_dir /path/to/epoch_N/

# Submit evaluation job
sbatch inspect.slurm

# View results interactively (on login node)
inspect view --port=$(get_free_port)
```

### Job Management
```bash
# View all your jobs
squeue -u <your_username>

# View recent job history
sacct -u <your_username> -S today --format=JobID,JobName,State,ExitCode,Elapsed,MaxRSS,End -X

# Cancel a job
scancel <job_id>

# Cancel all your jobs
scancel -u <your_username>
```

